Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da "karyar" ta hanyar "tallace-tallace"
Wata mako bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wata sanarwa mai shafuka hudu a cikin wata jaridar Amurka ta yau da kullum da ke nuna amfanin cinikin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka don yada labaransa.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana a ranar Laraba a cikin wani takarda mai biyan kuɗi na China Daily da ya bayyana a cikin Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a jihar Iowa, bayan ya zargi China da neman tsoma baki a zaben Majalisar Dinkin Duniya a ranar 6 ga Nuwamba, zargin da China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing ta yi ƙoƙarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka gaya wa Reuters cewa wani sabon mataki ne na yakin neman zabe da Washington ta kaddamar domin matsa lamba a kasar Sin.
Ko da yake ba a hana gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje yin tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwancinsu ba, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin faɗaɗa yaƙin kasuwanci kuma sun yi amfani da wasu haraji a kan shigo da kayayyaki.
Kungiyar 'yan kasuwa ta kasar Sin ta yi amfani da takunkumin da aka yi a farkon yakin kasuwanci don shafar masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa da ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, masana na kasar Sin da na Amurka sun ruwaito.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, wata jiha da ke fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kuma kamfanonin Amurka lahani.
Kamar yadda Branstadt ya rubuta a cikin wata sanarwa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register ta Lahadi, "China tana yin irin wannan barazanar ta wajen wallafa tallace-tallace masu ta'azama a cikin jaridarmu ta 'yanci".
"A ƙoƙarin yaɗa wannan labaran, gwamnatin China tana amfani da kyauta mai tamani na 'yancin magana da kuma 'yancin' yan jarida na Amirka ta hanyar yin tallan da aka biya a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A akasin haka, a cikin ofisoshin Beijing, za ku ga ƙarancin muryoyi masu banbanci da kuma wakilcin gaskiya na ra'ayoyi daban-daban da jama'ar kasar Sin za su iya yi game da matsalar tattalin arzikin kasar Sin, tun da yake kafofin watsa labarai suna karkashin ikon Jam'iyyar Kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
Ya ƙara da cewa "daya daga cikin manyan jaridu na kasar Sin ya ƙi yin tayin" ya buga labarinsa, ko da yake bai bayyana wanda ba.
